other_tests.findings: Liver parenchyma demonstrates normal echogenicity. There is mild intrahepatic biliary ductal dilatation. Common bile duct measures about 7 mm and tapers down to the head of the pancreas. No definite echogenic stone or mass is identified within the common bile duct. Gallbladder is distended and contains gallstones. There is no gallbladder wall thickening or pericholecystic fluid. Sonographic Murphy's sign is negative. Portal vein is patent.
